                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d188">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112/10618a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SWG1"
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sharp</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-10-11T17:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 11, 1918, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>5873. For <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_MG1">McFadden</persName> [from
                    War Trade Board]:</p>
                <p>No. 366. <persName>Stetson</persName>. Japan may soon request Paris and London
                    for inclusion in inter-Allied enemy trading listing and licensing committees on
                    basis principle unification of enemy trading lists and stricter administrative
                    control. England will assent to inclusion Japan if Japan requests it. We deem it
                    of great importance that Japan should participate conferences Paris and London,
                    as well as Washington. French Blockade representative, Washington, is
                    telegraphing his Government accordingly.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_PFL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
